body.p: CYP3A4 mediated conversion of DEX is responsible for the first-pass metabolism of DEX to MEM/MM3.

Vmax of export is defined relative to the `CYP3A4_Vmax` to ensure that the transport is fast relative to the absorption. This works because the `CYP3A4_Vmax` is on the same scale as the maximal absorption rate.

CYP3A4 mediated conversion of DEX is responsible for the first-pass metabolism of DEX, `dextromethorphan (DEX) -[CYP3A4]-> 3-methoxymorphinan (MEM/MM3)`.First pass can occur in intestine and liver and both enzymes are modeled via the same parameters (Km, Vmax).CYP3A4 inhibition/activation can be implemented by changing the `CYP3A4_activity`, e.g., grapefruit juice selectively inhibits only the intestinal CYP3A4.
